5:
Welcome to Smiles 101. I'm the teacher, 
Challua!
8: I look forward to our lesson, teacher.
18:
That's why I'm here! Stella's in good 
hands!
25:
Thanks to Regitare's lessons, I learned 
to talk! Knowledge is power!
29: Sure, but... a class about smiling?
43:
Yeah, that makes sense.
Especially coming from you, Challua.
64:
Uh, Stella? You don't need to write that 
one down.
68:
Lesson three! Get plenty of fluids... and 
pour them on your head!
72:
This lesson seems incredibly plant-
specific!
84:
Listen, Alk. I was once a nonbeliever 
like you.
85:
But I tried it out, and... this is 
surprisingly soothing. Perhaps it's the 
body, but I could get used to this.
94:
Lesson four! Cut off any excess 
branches!
99:
Oookay, I'm gonna stop you right 
there.
Could we get a HUMAN-specific lesson, 
by chance?
103:
Hmm. Humans and sprites not the 
same. I forgot!
109:
I'll make a new lesson soon! For 
humans!
116: Quite an odd pair, those two.
119:
Their backgrounds may be completely 
different, but they could totally be 
sisters.
122:
At first glance, Stella might seem like 
the responsible, older sister, but—
125:
Yeah, she's definitely the younger 
sister in this dynamic.
128: But I wonder if that's actually true?
131:
Say, Challua. How old are you, 
anyway?
138:
Umm... A hundred... A few thousand 
years? Somewhere in the thousands, 
I guess?
146: Does my time as a tree not count?
149:
Er, I'm not sure, actually. Let's just say 
it doesn't.
153:
In that case... Maybe ten? I don't 
remember when I became "me", 
exactly.
156:
I guess you can't really compare sprite 
ages to human ages, huh?
165:
Looks like it'll remain a mystery then—
which one of you two would be the 
"older sister".
171:
I have much to learn from Challua, 
so... I think it would be her.
174:
Me... a big sister? I've never had such 
a responsibility before...
177: Whoa, that's a pretty big word for you!
181:
I guess the Smiles 101 course was 
a success after all!
185: Wh-what? Did I say something wrong?
